						<h1>The Orcfax domain model</h1>
						<p class="mb-2">This <strong><a href="" class="text-primary">Orcfax domain model<a></strong> is a series of abstractions that describe aspects of the domain in which the <a href="https://orcfax.io" class="text-primary">Orcfax</a> blockchain oracle exists and can be used to solve problems related to Orcfax design, maintenance, and upgrades.</p>
						<h2>Domain Driven Design</h2>
						<p class="mb-2">Orcfax is a software-intensive system developed using <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Domain-driven_design" class="text-primary">Domain Driven Design</a> (DDD) concepts and practices from the software engineering discipline. DDD focuses on the subject area to which the software is applied. For Orcfax that includes collecting, validating, publishing and archiving real-world facts.</p>
						<p class="mb-2">A clear <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Domain_model" class="text-primary">domain model</a> is created as part of DDD methodology and it is the purpose of this website to define the Orcfax domain. This model is meant to be <a href="https://diataxis.fr/" class="text-primary">Reference documentation</a> to complement Orcfax's public <a href="https://docs.orcfax.io class="text-primary"">Explainer documentation</a>.</p>
						<h2>How to contribute</h2>
						<p class="mb-2">Please see <a href="https://github.com/orcfax/domain" class="text-primary">these instructions</a> if you want to discuss or suggest content for this domain model.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="col-xxl-6 col-sm-6 col-12">
						<div class="content-block">
						<h1>The Orcfax glossary</h1>
						<p class="mb-2">A key aspect of a domain model is the <a href="https://martinfowler.com/bliki/UbiquitousLanguage.html" class="text-primary">ubiquitious language</a> which is the shared terminology used by domain experts, software developers and end-users. We've formatted that here as the <strong><a href="" class="text-primary">Orcfax glossary</a></strong>, ie. a list of terms with clear definitions.</p>
						<p class="mb-2">
						<p class="mb-2">The Orcfax domain exists at a cross-section of a number of different domains for which we also maintain a <a href="" class="text-primary">glossary of external terms</a>.</p>
